  "text": "The activity of PLG was evaluated by the streptokinaseactivated PLG mediated proteolysis of chromogenic substrate S-2251 (H-D-Val-Leu-Lys-pNA; Boatman Biotech Co., Ltd, Shanghai, China). [CITATION_1] In brief, the plasma samples were diluted 40 times using 0.05 M Tris-HCl buffer (pH 7.4). A total of 50 mL of each diluted sample was then incubated with 50 mL streptokinase solution (5000 IU/mL) at 37 8C for 30 minutes in a 96-well plate. Then, 50 mL S-2251 (5 g/L) was added to the sample, and the absorbance of the wells was measured at 405 nm every 30 seconds for 30 minutes. PLG activity was determined by comparing the absorbance values of the samples with that of standard human plasma.",
